snippet.description:
This is a FAN/CONCEPT/PARODY FAN TRAILER. It's not an official or real FAN TRAILER. It's made for entertainment purposes only.

𝗚𝗲𝘁 𝗡𝗼𝗿𝗱𝗩𝗣𝗡: https://bit.ly/3cSyrYO

The inspiration behind this video: 

Will Eleven get another chance at defeating Vecna? Is Max going to wake up? Can Will ever find peace in his life? These were just some of my biggest questions going into Stranger Things season 5, Volume 1. Seeing as it has been over three years since Stranger Things season 4's ending, my list of lingering questions has become overwhelmingly long. But I guess good things do come to those who wait, because Volume 1's four episodes quickly answer some of my most burning questions.

Set a year and a half after the events of season 4, Stranger Things season 5 finds Hawkins under military control following the "earthquake" that tore apart the town, which was actually caused by Vecna. The villain hasn't been seen since he was thrown from a window with a shotgun blast, but that hasn't stopped the group from staying ready for Vecna's next move. While Hopper and Joyce are helping Eleven train, Mike, Will, Dustin, Lucas, Nancy, Jonathan, Steve, and Robin coordinate ways to locate Vecna. Max is still present, but she remains in a coma, serving as a reminder about how high the stakes are.

Thank You So Much For Watching!
Stay Tuned! Stay Buzzed!

──────────────────

snippet.title: The Lost Chapter: Yuki’s Revenge | Teaser Trailer
snippet.description:
Quentin Tarantino had a dream of a Kill Bill chapter that never made it to the silver screen, a chapter known as “Yuki’s Revenge.” Over 20 years later, Tarantino and Epic have come together to bring the story to life in Fortnite. 

Tarantino’s The Lost Chapter: Yuki’s Revenge stars Uma Thurman and premieres in Fortnite on November 30 at 2 PM ET! Doors open 30 minutes before the show starts. #fortnite #fortniteseven

Jason Statham returns as the enigmatic and deadly Beekeeper in this high-stakes sequel. This time, he faces a deeper conspiracy that threatens those he loves, pulling him into a deadly game with a ruthless new adversary, played by Jon Bernthal. 

As the lines blur between justice and revenge, the Beekeeper must navigate the world of organized crime, secret vendettas, and an unforgiving underworld.

With pulse-pounding action sequences, gritty fight choreography, and a tense atmosphere, The Beekeeper 2 promises a heart-racing ride. The stakes are higher, the enemies more dangerous, and the cost of vengeance even greater.

snippet.title: Who thought this was a good idea..
snippet.description:
Asmongold Clips / Asmongold Reacts To: Emiru gets 1000 gifted subs after Twitch introduced the new package, which has already gotten removed after 1 day..


On this Asmongold Clips Youtube Channel you'll never quit finding all the funny Asmongold Moments with Mcconnell and the best Asmongold Highlights from the most popular games, like: Baldur's Gate 3, Helldivers 2, Starfield, Blizzard Diablo 4, The War Within & Hardcore Classic WoW, the record breaking MMORPG FFXIV, Path of Exile 2, sneak peeks from Gameplay of the upcoming Riot MMO and playthroughs of many other popular games like Monster Hunter, Final Fantasy 16, Elden Ring and more. Also Asmongold Reacts to a lot of content, such as World Record Speed Run of games, Drama and videos of some of the most interesting creators like penguinz0, Internet Historian, Emiru, Dunkey and more. Asmon is also known for his "The True Story of Asmongold", "Asmongold $2 Pizza" and "Asmongold $2 Steak", "Asmongold Room and House Tour" videos, the legendary Transmog Competitions and Mount Off competitions, Ban Appeals, Media Share streams, Reddit Recap Reactions and much more.

► Twitch: https://www.twitch.tv/zackrawrr

Then turn around, say that I'm the worst thing?

And you're Ms. "Never Do No Wrong"
If I'm so awful
Then why'd you stick around this long?

We try to go our sеparate ways
And we're back and forth likе a swingin' door

And you're back with me again
Then you go and tell your friends

[Chorus]
That I'm the problem
And you're Ms. "Never Do No Wrong"
If I'm so awful
Then why'd you stick around this long?
